Around 3.72 million hectares of wheat have been harvested in major summer grain-producing areas of China, according to the wheat harvest schedule released by the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Affairs (MARA) on May 31. The summer harvest is underway from south to north in major producing areas. Bao Dongsheng is a photographer living in Yuncheng, Shanxi Province, where the bumper summer harvest has started. In this video, he introduces the process of the wheat harvest, including reaping, drying of grain and the recycling of straw.